  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (NC-9 clean)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification is performed. All 13 credibility factors are assessed with achieved levels meeting or exceeding required levels. One factor (Model inputs) carries explicitly low confidence due to limited rheological data; this gap is honestly documented with full rationale and a sensitivity analysis demonstrating bounded impact. Decision: Accepted with documented residual uncertainty.",
